<p class="govuk-body">
  This pattern lets the user change the language used in a service from English to Welsh and from Welsh
  to English.
</p>

<h2 id="when-to-use" class="govuk-heading-l">When to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Use the Welsh language toggle when a service is available in Welsh.
</p>

<h2 id="when-not-to-use" class="govuk-heading-l">When not to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Do not use the Welsh language toggle:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>where there is no Welsh translation for a service</li>
  <li>in personal tax account services â€“ use the
  <a class="govuk-link" href="/design-library/account-header">account header</a> which already has a
  Welsh language toggle</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="how-it-works" class="govuk-heading-l">How it works</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Put the Welsh language toggle on the right hand side below the
  <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/header/">GOV.UK header</a>.
</p>

{{
